raw_meta_yaml:
context:
  name: awslambdaric
  version: '3.1.1'

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  - url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/awslambdaric-${{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 1c1fd30570b9a2c5cc4ccd2151c883312c5eef2dbf759c8e9d29c18cec6de2e8
  # Please see awslabs/aws-lambda-cpp#94, remove once aws-lambda-cpp is upgraded to 0.2.7
    patches:
      - if: linux
        then:
          - aws-lambda-cpp-0.2.6-update-backward-cpp.patch
  - if: linux
    then:
      - url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bombela/backward-cpp/v1.6/backward.hpp
        sha256: 404aa26ecc36be08f92c03b05505561e064f6f1f7cffcbda77a7d4959e4c07f2
        target_directory: deps/patches
        file_name: backward.h

build:
  script: ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 1

requirements:
  build:
    - if: linux
      then:
        - ${{ compiler('c') }}
        - ${{ stdlib('c') }}
        - ${{ compiler('cxx') }}
        - automake
        - autoconf
        - cmake
        - libtool
        - make
        - pkg-config
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - python
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
    - simplejson >=3.20.1
    - snapshot-restore-py >=1.0.0

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - awslambdaric
      pip_check: true

about:
  homepage: https://github.com/aws/aws-lambda-python-runtime-interface-client
  summary: AWS Lambda Runtime Interface Client for Python
  license: BSD-3-Clause AND Apache-2.0
  license_file:
    - LICENSE
    - THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - raybellwaves
    - sodre
    - '0xbe7a'
    - pavelzw
